docs.abstract: As chief executives hunker down during the pandemic, home offices have become corporate headquarters.
docs.snippet: As chief executives hunker down during the pandemic, home offices have become corporate headquarters.
docs.lead_paragraph: On Thursday morning, Chuck Robbins, the chief executive of Cisco, signed on to an companywide video conference from his home office in Silicon Valley. The connection was stable, but the quality was not great.

headline.main: Logged On From the Laundry Room: How the C.E.O.s of Google, Pfizer and Slack Work From Home

docs.abstract: Will the company’s chief executive, Jack Dorsey, lose his job?
docs.snippet: Will the company’s chief executive, Jack Dorsey, lose his job?
docs.lead_paragraph: Elon Musk was right in his tweet this week: Jack Dorsey does have a “good ❤️.” Mr. Dorsey is indeed one of the more thoughtful, responsive and earnest entrepreneurs in Silicon Valley.

headline.main: Brace Yourself for What’s Coming at Twitter
